The data layer is deliberately separated from the UI layer

data.js owns everything about where items live and how they're
fetched/stored. app.js and form.js own the DOM — reading form
fields, rendering cards, showing toasts, validating input.

Neither UI file talks to a server or an array directly. They only ever
call getItems() or createItem(payload). This means: when the backend
exists, only data.js changes. Nothing in app.js or form.js needs to
be touched.


//getItem has been made async to make things easy in the implementation of the backend


//id and date are also auto generated this function must be moved and connected from the backend

